sql:
SELECT team_id, season
FROM defensive_performance
WHERE passing_yards_allowed > 300 AND defensive_touchdowns >= 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Titans of defense" refers to teams with the best defensive performance;
- "Fewest passing yards allowed" means the defense allowed the least number of passing yards;
- "Most sacks" means the defense recorded the highest number of sacks;
- "Most interceptions" means the defense intercepted the most passes.

- "points returned" refers to the points scored by the defense through actions like safeties and defensive touchdowns;
- "passing yards allowed" refers to the total yards gained by the opposing team's passing plays;
- "regular season" refers to the main part of the NFL season, excluding playoffs and Super Bowl.

- "Points returned" in football refers to points scored by a team's defense, often through turnovers or special teams plays;
- "DENSE_RANK()" is used to rank teams within each season, ensuring that ties receive the same rank and the next rank is the next consecutive number;
- "Season" refers to the specific year and part of the year (e.g., 2022 regular season) in which the games were played.

- The "2023 season" refers to the year 2023 in the context of the sports league's schedule;
- "Week 1" is the first week of the regular season in the 2023 schedule;
- "Game outcome" is determined by the score, where a higher score indicates a win, a lower score indicates a loss, and equal scores indicate a tie.

- "least number of passing yards allowed" refers to the team allowing the fewest passing yards to the opposing team;
- "fewest passing touchdowns conceded" refers to the team conceding the fewest passing touchdowns;
- "most defensive touchdowns" refers to the team scoring the most defensive touchdowns;
- "beacon of defensive excellence" symbolizes the team with the best overall defensive performance, as measured by the sum of ranks in passing yards allowed, passing touchdowns allowed, and defensive touchdowns scored.

sql:
SELECT team_id, AVG(passing_yards_allowed) AS average_passing_yards_allowed
FROM defensive_performance
GROUP BY team_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Top 5" refers to the best five teams based on the specified performance metrics;
- "Average points returned" measures the team's defensive performance in terms of points;
- "Average passing touchdowns allowed" measures the team's defensive performance against passing plays;
- "Total defensive touchdowns" measures the team's defensive performance in scoring.

- "guardian of the last line of defense" refers to the team with the best defensive performance;
- "allowing the fewest passing yards" refers to the lowest average passing yards allowed;
- "returning the most points" refers to the highest average points returned.

sql:
SELECT MAX(points_returned_total) AS max_points_returned
FROM (
  SELECT SUM(points_returned) AS points_returned_total
  FROM defensive_performance
  GROUP BY team_id
);

external_knowledge:
- 'Defensive prowess' refers to the average defensive points returned, average passing yards allowed, and average number of sacks;
- 'Victories' are indicated by a score ending in 'W';
- 'Support they receive at home' refers to the average attendance for home games.

- "guardians of the gridiron" refers to teams with strong defensive performance;
- "highest average defensive prowess" refers to the highest average in sacks, interceptions, or defensive touchdowns;
- Defensive performance metrics include sacks, interceptions, and defensive touchdowns.

- 'stand tall in the echelon of victory' refers to teams with a high win rate;
- 'hierarchy of triumph' refers to the ranking based on the win rate;
- The win rate is calculated as the number of wins divided by the total number of games played.

- "guardian of the year" refers to the team with the best defensive performance;
- "standing tall and firm with the least points returned" indicates the team with the lowest average points returned by their defense;
- "record of at least 5 defensive performances" means the team must have at least 5 entries in the defensive performance table for the 2023 season.

- "Defensive statistics" include passing yards allowed, passing touchdowns allowed, and sacks;
- "Overall defensive statistics" are calculated by averaging the statistics across all teams within the same conference and division;
- The rankings are based on the overall average passing yards allowed and overall average sacks, with higher values indicating poorer defensive performance in terms of passing yards allowed and better performance in terms of sacks.
